, participation, and negotiation, and the findings demonstrate the complex ways in which novices transform communities in transnational contexts. The perspectives inform the fields of second language acquisition and language maintenance and shift. The book further provides a rare glimpse of the "idian negotiations of adoptive family life and suggestions for supporting adoptees as young bilinguals.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aAdoptionvCase studies. 0aAdoptionxCase studies. 0aBilingualismvCase studies. 0aBilingualismxCase studies. 0aCode switching (Linguistics)vCase studies. 0aCode switching (Linguistics)xCase studies. 0aEnglish languagexCase studiesxStudy and teachingxRussian speakers. 0aEnglish languagexStudy and teachingxRussian speakersvCase studies. 0aSecond language acquisitionvCase studies. 0aSecond language acquisitionxCase studies. 0aSocializationvCase studies. 0aSocializationxCase studies. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aRussia.  aadoption.  alanguage acquisition.  alanguage education.  asocialization.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066313608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014z978311060671340uhttps://doi.org/10.21832/978184769786840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781847697868423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781847697868/original  a978-3-11-060671-3  MultiLingual Matters eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014c2000d2014  a978-3-11-066313-6  MultiLingual Matters Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGru